DESCRIPTION:Branner Earth Sciences Library & Map Collection exhibit series:
  Oceans\n\nIn the 2025–2026 academic year\, Branner Library’s exhibit serie
 s will explore Earth’s oceans’ complex biological and ecological systems th
 at regulate climate and support life.\n\nFebruary's exhibition explores how
  ocean structure\, sea ice processes\, and ecological interactions govern A
 rctic systems\, influence global climate feedbacks\, and shape emerging env
 ironmental\, scientific\, and societal challenges in a rapidly changing Arc
 tic Ocean.\n\nFeaturing books\, e-resources\, and maps\, the exhibition dem
 onstrates why the Arctic is central to advancing understanding of global cl
 imate dynamics\, biodiversity\, and human–environment interactions in a war
 ming world.\n\nThe exhibit is available for viewing Monday through Friday d
 uring regular library open hours. \nCheck out past exhibits and subscribe t
 o the Branner Library Newsletter.  \n\nA current Stanford ID is needed to e
 nter the library\, visitors must present a valid\, physical government-issu
 ed photo ID to sign-in at the front desk.
