BEGIN:VEVENT
CATEGORIES:Tour,Lecture/Presentation/Talk
DESCRIPTION:Join Jason Linetzky\, Museum Director at the Anderson Collectio
 n\, on this special tour of Alteronce Gumby. \n\nThe Anderson Collection pr
 esents the first West Coast museum exhibition of New York–based artist Alte
 ronce Gumby. Featuring nine recent works\, the show celebrates Gumby’s ongo
 ing investigation of color\, the cosmos\, and abstraction. Drawing inspirat
 ion from artists represented in the Anderson Collection\, such as Mark Roth
 ko and Joan Mitchell\, Gumby’s luminous\, textured surfaces extend the lega
 cies of 20th-century American painting while forging a distinctly contempor
 ary path. The exhibition is on view in the Wisch Family Gallery from Septem
 ber 24\, 2025-March 1\, 2026.\n\nAlteronce Gumby is a contemporary abstract
  painter interested in the history of monochromatic painting\, color theory
 \, cosmology\, astrophysics\, and interstellar photography. Gumby’s process
  is the fulcrum of his work. It begins with the examination of light and it
 s properties\, and media including resin\, glass and gemstones. This unorth
 odox blend of materials results in works Gumby calls “tonal paintings”\, ea
 ch producing unique hues\, values and energies. Dynamic and vibrant\, Gumby
 ’s paintings propose an expanded understanding of abstraction\, color\, lif
 e and the origins of the universe. Gumby graduated from the Yale School of 
 Art with an MFA in Painting and Printmaking in 2016. He has won notable awa
 rds such as the Austrian American Foundation/ Seebacher Prize for Fine Arts
  and the Robert Reed Memorial Scholarship. Gumby has also participated in n
 umerous international artist residencies such as the Rauschenberg Residency
  (2019)\, London Summer Intensive (2016)\, Summer Academy in Salzburg\, Aus
 tria (2015)\, 6Base (2016)\, Harriet Hale Woolley Scholarship at the Fondat
 ion des Étas-Unis in Paris (2016) and is the 2024-2025 recipient of the pre
 stigious Pollock-Krasner Foundation grant for artists.\n\nRSVP here.
DTEND:20260209T220000Z
DTSTAMP:20260308T083906Z
DTSTART:20260209T210000Z
GEO:37.433768;-122.170791
LOCATION:Anderson Collection\, Wisch Gallery
SEQUENCE:0
