DESCRIPTION:Redistricting 101: California’s Prop 50 and beyond!\n\nJoin the
  Stanford University Libraries for an interactive redistricting mapping wor
 kshop during Love Data Week! On Tuesday Nov. 4th\, California’s voters weig
 hed in on Proposition 50\, a state constitutional amendment to modify Congr
 essional district maps. Come on by our hands-on workshop on how to make you
 r own mathematically-sound redistricting map. What does democratic represen
 tation look like? The choice is yours.\n\nWe will be using online cartograp
 hic tools like DRA (Dave’s Redistricting) and PlanScore to draw and evaluat
 e voting district maps.\n\nGuest speaker Mike Migurski will share how PlanS
 core participates in the redistricting process!\n\nPlease register here! Th
 is workshop will take place in-person in the Green Library IC Classroom.\n\
 nLearn about: \n\nProposition 50: The Election Rigging Response Act Measure
 s of fairnessCensus DataPartisan versus independent redistricting commissio
 nsFor those attending the in-person event\, please bring your Stanford ID c
 ard or mobile ID to enter the library.\n\nWe will be taking photos at this 
 event for publicity purposes. Your presence at this event constitutes conse
 nt to be photographed unless you express otherwise.
