 into the space\, from early curiosity to real-world impact. With diverse ba
 ckgrounds and starting points\, panelists will reflect on what drew them to
  energy\, what they’ve learned along the way\, and how they’ve explored sta
 rtups\, technology commercialization\, and other pathways to scale solution
 s. \n\nThis session is designed for anyone exploring energy innovation and 
 will highlight why the field matters\, how it connects to pressing global c
 hallenges\, and the Stanford Ecopreneurship resources available to you.\n\n
 Join this session to hear from and join breakout sessions with Stanford all
