CATEGORIES:Lecture/Presentation/Talk
DESCRIPTION:In a new report for the Council on Foreign Relations\, America 
 Revived\, Ambassador Blackwill argues that the United States faces the most
  dangerous international environment since World War II. He defines U.S. vi
 tal national interests\, summarizes the history of American grand strategy\
 , outlines and critiques five grand strategy schools (primacy\, liberal int
 ernationalism\, restraint\, American nationalism\, and Trumpism)\, and adva
 nces a new grand strategy—resolute global leadership. This approach merges 
 the military power and global presence of primacy with the alliance network
 s\, institutional engagement\, and focus on legitimacy emphasized by libera
 l internationalism.
DTEND:20260210T210000Z
DTSTAMP:20260308T083906Z
DTSTART:20260210T200000Z
