CATEGORIES:Exhibition
DESCRIPTION:Romance is one of the richest – and one of the very oldest – ve
 ins of storytelling. It’s multifarious\, intercultural\, transhistorical…an
 d at the same time reliant on characters\, tropes\, plot structures\, and s
 torytelling strategies that have persisted in their appeal to audiences thr
 ough the centuries. This month’s Special\, Unique\, and Rare pop-up exhibit
  offers some fascinating examples from Stanford Libraries’ collections of R
 OMANCE – courtly\, divine\, doomed\, epistolary\, unrequited\, and so much 
 more – to dally with for a moment or two. \n\nDrop in any time between 2-4 
 PM on Tuesday\, February  10th\, Hohbach 123 (Silicon Valley Archive classr
 oom\, Green Library).\n\nFor once-a-monthly notifications about upcoming Sp
 ecial\, Unique & Rare pop-up exhibits\, join our mailing list.
DTEND:20260211T000000Z
DTSTAMP:20260308T083906Z
DTSTART:20260210T220000Z
GEO:37.426984;-122.167998
LOCATION:Green Library\, Bing Wing\, Hohbach Hall 123 (1st floor\, East Win
 g)
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:Special\, Unique\, and Rare: ROMANCE
