CATEGORIES:Conference/Symposium,Social Event/Reception
DESCRIPTION:Join us on February 10\, 2026 from 3:30 p.m. - 5:30 p.m. in the
  Hartley Conference Room\, Mitchell Earth Sciences Building to celebrate th
 e work of the SDSS Dean's Graduate Scholars and the SDSS Dean's Sustainabil
 ity Leaders Postdocs. As part of Love Data Week with the Stanford Universit
 y Libraries\, we are highlighting the work of the Doerr School of Sustainab
 ility Dean's Scholars in this special research symposium.\n\nThe symposium 
 will consist of lightning talks given by students and postdocs (see below)\
 , followed by a reception with light refreshments.\n\nRegistration required
  through Luma.\n\nProgram Itinerary\n\n3:30-3:40pm | Opening Remarks and In
 troductions3:50-5:00pm | Speaker PresentationsCatherine Lee Hing | Ph.D. ca
 ndidate | E-IPEREvolution of Traditional Fishing in the CaribbeanJordan Tuc
 ker | Master's candidate | GeophysicsDifferentiating sea ice properties usi
 ng coincident observationsStephanie Caddell | Ph.D. student | OceansProtect
 ing juvenile Loggerheads: Evaluating bycatch risk in North Pacific foraging
  areasElsie Carillo | Postdoctoral Scholar | OceansA bubble for trouble: Na
 rial bubble "rebreathing" as an alternate mechanism for extending time unde
 rwater in Garter snakesAarabhi Achanta | Ph.D. student | Earth System Scien
 ceAgent-based modeling of food market dynamics under climate variability in
  KarnatakaKatie Huy | Ph.D. candidate | Earth System ScienceImpact of presc
 ribed fire on soil C and N cyclingMario Ruiz Moreno | Ph.D. candidate | Geo
 physicsInside an explosion: Linking volcano physics to what geophyscists me
 asure on the groundAlexis Hensley | Ph.D. student | GeophysicsProspecting f
 or 3HE on the moon using regolith magnetic susceptibility measurements​​​​​
 ​​5:00-5:30pm | Reception - Everyone is invited!SDSS Dean’s Grad Scholars A
 ward Program\n\nThe SDSS Dean’s Grad Scholars Program award and professiona
 l development to support the first year of graduate school at the Doerr Sch
 ool for incoming MS and PhD student who excel academically and also display
  leadership in creating inclusive academic spaces in the sciences. \n\nSDSS
  Dean’s Sustainability Leaders Postdoctoral Fellowship\n\nThe SDSS Dean’s S
 ustainability Leaders Postdoctoral Fellowship is a two year fellowship for 
 Postdoctoral Fellows who demonstrate research excellence in advancing field
 s reflected across the Doerr and have a track record of creating inclusive 
 science through teaching\, research and/or leadership.\n\nThis event is co-
 hosted by Stanford University Libraries and the Stanford Doerr School of Su
 stainability Office of Access\, Belonging\, and Community\, as part of Stan
 ford Love Data Week\, an annual festival highlighting topics\, opportunitie
 s and services relevant to data in research.\n\nWe will be taking photos at
  this event for publicity purposes. Your presence at this event constitutes
  consent to be photographed unless you express otherwise.
