CATEGORIES:Film/Screening
DESCRIPTION:About the event\n\nSouth Asia Working Group (SAWG) together wit
 h Stanford Sri Lankan Association (SSLA) present Ayu\, a Sri Lankan film di
 rected by Chathra Weeraman starring Sandra Mack\, Jagath Manuwarna\, Ashan 
 Dias\, Malini Fonseka and Kenara Weeratunga. Ayu\, tells the story of Nishm
 i (Sandra Mack)\, a paediatrician who survives a life-altering accident but
  is left emotionally adrift in its aftermath. \n\nMusic by Milinda Tennakoo
 ne.\n\nProduction Design by Bimal Dushmantha.\n\nUS Distribution courtesy o
 f Gayesha Perera Films.\n\nRuntime: 1 hour and 56 minutes\n\nAbout the Dire
 ctor\n\nBorn in Colombo\, Sri Lanka\, Chathra Weeraman is a graduate of Cin
 ematic Arts. Chathra began his career initially as a CG artist and later we
 nt on to offer on-set VFX supervision for films. His career took a sharp tu
 rn when his directorial debut saw the light of day. The Biopic ‘Aloko Udapa
 di’ (Light Arose) gained much hype from the mass audience of Sri Lanka and 
 was critically acclaimed. The film premiered at the 47th International Film
  Festival of India\, 9th Bengaluru International Film Festival and 20th Sha
 nghai International Film Festival.\n\nCheck out Ayu (2025) trailer here.\n\
 nRegistration is required.
