DESCRIPTION:WiDS Stanford @ Lane Medical Library is independently organized
  by Lane Medical Library to be part of the mission to increase the particip
 ation of women in data science and to feature outstanding women doing outst
 anding work.\n\nWiDS @ Lane aims to inspire\, engage\, and support data sci
 entists and women in the field. Join us for this half-day virtual conferenc
 e on Wednesday\, February 11\, 2026\, our eight annual event. This year's t
 heme: \nReady\, FAIR\, Go! Making Clinical and Biomedical Data Findable\, A
 ccessible\, Interoperable\, Reusable. Speakers will share insights on chall
 enges\, successes\, and emerging trends\, and offer inspiration and practic
 al strategies for advancing the field of data science. \n\nThe event will b
 e recorded via Zoom. Registration is free and open to the public. All gende
 rs are welcome and encouraged to attend.\n\nConference Agenda:\n\n9:00 - 9:
 10 Welcome & Opening Remarks\n\n9:10 - 10:00 Opening Keynote by Marina Siro
 ta\, PhD\, Professor at UCSF\, Acting Director\, Bakar Computational Health
  Sciences Institute\n\n10:00 - 11:05 Panel Discussion and Q & A with:\n\nTe
 resa Zayas Cabán\, PhD\, Assistant Director for Policy Development\, Nation
 al Library of MedicineAshley Griffin\, PhD\, MSPH\, Instructor\, Stanford U
 niversity Division of Computational Medicine\,  Investigator\, VA Palo Alto
  Health Care System\, Center for Innovation to ImplementationDaniella Meeke
 r\, PhD\, Associate Professor of Biomedical Informatics & Data Science\, Ya
 le School of Medicine11:05 - 11:10 Break\n\n11:10 - 12:05 Closing Keynote b
 y Ericka Johnson\, PhD\, MPhil\, Professor\, Linköping University\, WASP-HS
  graduate school director\, Wallenberg AI\, Autonomous Systems and Software
  Program – Humanity and Society\n\n12:05 - 12:10 Wrap-up\n\nKeynotes by Mar
 ina Sirota & Ericka Johnson
