CATEGORIES:
DESCRIPTION:Join us for Lane Medical Library’s eighth annual Women in Data 
 Science (WiDS) regional conference. “Ready\, FAIR\, Go! Making Clinical and
  Biomedical Data Findable\, Accessible\, Interoperable\, Reusable”  is this
  year’s theme for the half-day virtual conference. The event will explore h
 ow women are incorporating FAIR data principles into their work. This year\
 , our conference coincides with Love Data Week\, a week-long celebration of
  all things data-related. There will be other data science events and works
 hops on campus throughout the week!\n\nWiDS Stanford @ Lane Medical Library
  is independently organized by Lane Medical Library to be part of the missi
 on to increase the participation of women in data science and to feature ou
 tstanding women doing outstanding work.  You can explore all of the Women i
 n Data Science events worldwide on the WiDS website.\n\nRegister today to s
 ave the date! Registration is free and open to the Stanford Medicine commun
 ity and beyond.
