DESCRIPTION:Assuming favorable weather\, we will station a solar telescope 
 with an appropriate and safe filter outside of Green Library that can be us
 ed to view the Sun. A solar physicist from Stanford’s JSOC will be on hand 
 to answer questions about the sun and ensure telescope safety.\n\nIn case o
 f poor weather\, we will also display a timelapse video of the Sun on a scr
 een within Green Library\, so you can see the dynamic surface of the sun an
 d its rotation.\n\nInterested in the sun? ☀️ On February 10th\, join us for
  a discussion of Stanford’s 50 Years of history collecting and studying sol
 ar data. Then\, on February 11th\, learn how to access and use solar data b
 y joining our SunPy workshop.\n\nDate and Time: 10:00–2:00PM\, Wednesday\, 
 February 11\, 2026Location: Entrance\, Hohbach Hall\, Green LibrarySolar Ph
 ysicists: Charles Baldner\, Cristina Rabello Soares\, Alex KoufosOrganizes:
  Katie FreyThis event is part of Love Data Week\, an annual festival highli
 ghting topics\, opportunities and services relevant to data in research.
