BEGIN:VEVENT
CATEGORIES:Lecture/Presentation/Talk
DESCRIPTION:As the United States approaches its 250th anniversary\, this sp
 ecial panel\, presented in collaboration with Stanford’s College 102 progra
 m\, the Hoover Institution\, and the Department of History\, examines the t
 raditions that have shaped the American experiment and the debates that con
 tinue to define it.\n\nThe discussion will explore classical and Enlightenm
 ent influences on American political thought\, the legacy of slavery\, and 
 how competing interpretations of the past shape contemporary civic life. Fo
 llowing introductory remarks by Stephen Kotkin\, the program will feature p
 resentations by Barry Strauss\, Caroline Winterer\, Dan Edelstein\, and Ann
 e Twitty\, with Jonathan Gienapp moderating a rigorous and civic exchange g
 rounded in open inquiry and respectful disagreement.
DTEND:20260212T040000Z
DTSTAMP:20260308T083906Z
DTSTART:20260212T020000Z
