BEGIN:VEVENT
CATEGORIES:Social Event/Reception
DESCRIPTION:Take a moment to relax with snacks\, crafts\, and games at Bran
 ner Earth Sciences Library! \n\nThis event is part of Love Data Week at Sta
 nford\, an annual festival highlighting topics\, opportunities and services
  relevant to data in research. So grab a coffee while you create your own d
 ata inspired crafts!\n\nAvailable activities:\n\nAI APIs & Astronomy Imager
 y - Compare real astronomical photos from Astronomy Picture of the Day (APo
 D) with AI images we generate on demand for you from Stanford's AI Playgrou
 nd API. Check out last year's gallery.Map Embroidery - Make a meaningful ma
 p in this data physicalization activity! We provide the raw materials for y
 ou to embroider a personal mini-map\, you bring the creativity. Textile Dat
 a Weaving - You’re probably used to seeing data represented in charts and g
 raphs\, but have you ever seen a data set turned into a textile? With this 
 activity\, you can weave a data set into cloth to destress and learn a fun 
 method of displaying data.Guess the Dataset! - Try to guess the underlying 
 dataset from an unlabeled graph. This is a fun way to put your knowledge of
  trends in the world to the test. We'll put it up on a bit screen so you ca
 n play with your friends\, and maybe make some new friends! All activities 
 are free\, no experience necessary (we'll show you how!)\, and will be avai
 lable while supplies last!\n\nHelp us reduce waste\, bring your own covered
  mug and reusable plate!\nBranner Library will also be hosting several data
  inspired events throughout the day\, be sure to check them out!\n\nPlease 
 bring your Stanford ID card/mobile ID to enter the library\, visitors must 
 present their government issued ID at the front desk.\n\nWe will be taking 
 photos at this event for publicity purposes. Your presence at this event co
 nstitutes consent to be photographed unless you express otherwise.
DTEND:20260212T220000Z
DTSTAMP:20260308T083906Z
DTSTART:20260212T180000Z
