CATEGORIES:Workshop
DESCRIPTION:Data Farm is Stanford University's research data exploration\, 
 extraction\, and analysis tool for datasets. Stanford contracts with Redivi
 s for use of their SaaS platform for storing\, distributing\, and analyzing
  research data. Redivis offers a modern\, high-performance web-based interf
 ace that enables researchers to work with a wide variety of datasets. \n\nW
 hat can Data Farm do?\n\nData Farm allows highly efficient and fast queries
  (using either the visual query editor or writing SQL) directly in the brow
 ser. After performing a query\, such as: filter-aggregate-combine\, you can
  explore descriptive statistics and visualizations right away or move into 
 integrated notebooks for further data manipulation.\n\nDatasets on Data Far
 m are interoperable with common data analysis tools such as: Python\, R\, S
 AS\, and Stata and can be easily exported to on-premise computing environme
 nts such as Farmshare / Sherlock into cloud compute services like GCP\, AWS
 \, Azure\, or downloaded for local analysis (usage rights permitting).\n\nD
 ate and Time: 2:00PM–3:00PM\, Thursday\, February 12\, 2026Location: Zoom (
 link provided upon registration) and Velma Denning Room (120F)\, Bing Wing\
 , Green LibraryLead Instructor:  Ian Matthews (CEO\, Redivis) & Vijoy Abrah
 am (Assistant University Librarian\, Research Data Services\, Stanford Univ
 ersity Libraries)This event is part of Love Data Week\, an annual festival 
 highlighting topics\, opportunities and services relevant to data in resear
 ch.
