BEGIN:VEVENT
CATEGORIES:Lecture/Presentation/Talk
DESCRIPTION:With Guest Speaker Allison Carruth (Professor of American Studi
 es and Environmental Studies\, Princeton University)\n\nThis workshop will 
 explore the emergence of ecomedia studies as a cross-cutting subfield of bo
 th STS and the environmental humanities by way of a discussion of a recent 
 stream published in the open-access journal Media + Environment on “Modelin
 g the Pacific Ocean”. The seminar will then share some of the work of Princ
 eton’s Blue Lab as a case study in the creative environmental humanities. C
 ofounded by Allison Carruth and Barron Bixler\, Blue Lab is the country's o
 nly media production studio located at a research university that focuses o
 n climate and environment storytelling. Since 2021\, Blue Lab has built a m
 ultidisciplinary team\, fostered a network of collaborators and advisors\, 
 launched a major public art program and developed five original story proje
 cts (three podcasts\, a documentary film currently in production and a nonf
 iction dispatch series about uncanny coastal places). The lab aims to equip
  scientists and humanists alike with the training and tools to amplify the 
 reach of their vital work beyond academic journals\, conferences\, monograp
 hs and classrooms. The lab’s method is to mobilize environmental research i
 n the service of telling stories that are hyperlocal\, aesthetically captiv
 ating and geared toward connecting with audiences across some critical cult
 ural divides. With these examples of ecomedia scholarship and creative prac
 tice as models\, the final part of the workshop will be structured around b
 reakouts in which groups develop the initial ideas—and outline some of the 
 practical challenges and ethical considerations—for an ecomedia project bas
 ed in California.\n\nRSVP HERE for Interdisciplinary Workshop: Ecomedia Inc
 ubator
DTEND:20260213T020000Z
