BEGIN:VEVENT
CATEGORIES:Lecture/Presentation/Talk
DESCRIPTION:Please join the French-Speaking Worlds: Then and Now for a talk
  entitled "Friedrich Nietzsche\, a Poet\, and the French Revolution" by Gui
 llaume Métayer (CNRS). \n\nAbstract: \nFriedrich Nietzsche took an astoundi
 ngly early interest in French culture and especially in the French Revoluti
 on. It is one of the haunting themes of his early poems\, in particular aro
 und 1862. How can we understand this early fascination? What were its sourc
 es? Through an investigation focused mainly on the poem “Im Gefängnis” (“In
  Prison”)\, dedicated to the legendary account of the death of the Girondin
 s\, we will attempt to better understand Nietzsche’s relationship with Fran
 ce and its history\, while also identifying the philosophical and ideologic
 al implications of his poetic interpretation of it.\n\nBio:\nGuillaume Méta
 yer is a research director at the CNRS within the CELLF (Sorbonne Universit
 é\, Paris). His research focuses on the reception of the Enlightenment at t
 he turn of the 19th and 20th centuries\, and especially on Friedrich Nietzs
 che and Anatole France and his circle\, like the Hungarian woman writer Ott
 ilia Bölöni. He is also a translator of German\, Hungarian and Slovenian po
 etry and the author of an essay on translation (A like in Babel\, 2020) and
  some books of poems.\n\nRSVP for talk by Guillaume Métayer\n\nHosted by th
 e French-Speaking Worlds: Then and Now Focal Group\, sponsored by the Divis
 ion of Literatures\, Cultures\, and Languages Research Unit and co-sponsore
 d by the France-Stanford Center and Stanford Global Studies. This event is 
 part of Stanford Global Studies’ Global Research Workshop Program.
DTEND:20260213T023000Z
DTSTAMP:20260308T083907Z
DTSTART:20260213T010000Z
GEO:37.427405;-122.1697
LOCATION:Building 260\, Pigott Hall\, 216
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:French-Speaking Worlds: "Friedrich Nietzsche\, a Poet\, and the Fre
 nch Revolution" by Guillaume Métayer (CNRS)
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_51905501888986
URL:https://events.stanford.edu/event/french-speaking-worlds-friedrich-niet
 zsche-a-poet-and-the-french-revolution-by-guillaume-metayercnrs
