BEGIN:VEVENT
CATEGORIES:Lecture/Presentation/Talk
DESCRIPTION:Want to understand how LGBTQ+ visibility is used to obscure opp
 ression and injustice?\n\nJoin the Stanford Women's Community Center for th
 e first event of our Collective Liberation Series:\n\nPinkwashing 101: A Te
 ach-In with Mama Ganuush\, a trans Palestinian performance artist\, drag qu
 eer\, filmmaker\, and organizer\, in a facilitated discussion on combating 
 pinkwashing.\n\nThis teach-in will unpack the concept of pinkwashing\, how 
 corporations and states deploy LGBTQ+ rights language to appear progressive
  while masking harmful policies and human rights abuses. \n\nIn this intera
 ctive teach-in\, we will:\n1. Explore the origins and history of pinkwashin
 g\n2. Examine real-world examples across corporate branding and state polit
 ics\n3. Center queer\, trans\, and Palestinian perspectives often erased fr
 om mainstream narratives\n4. Build shared language to critically engage in 
 collective liberation \n\nWhether you’re involved in organizing\, curious a
 bout queer politics\, or looking to deepen your analysis of power and repre
 sentation\, this teach-in offers information and tools you can carry into y
 our communities.\n\n \n\nRSVP? Here! *Food available while supplies last* S
 ee you there\, Thursday\, February 12th\, at 6:30 pm!\n\n \n\nCo-sponsors: 
 Stanford's Center for Comparative Studies in Race & Ethnicity\, Stanford's 
 Program in Feminist Gender\, and Sexuality Studies\,  the Institute for Div
 ersity in the Arts\, Queer Student Resources\n\nHosted by: Stanford Women's
  Community Center. \n\n \n\nQuestions? Reach out to the Collective Liberati
 on Coordinator\, lizbethz@stanford.edu.
DTEND:20260213T040000Z
DTSTAMP:20260308T083907Z
DTSTART:20260213T023000Z
GEO:37.425085;-122.171682
LOCATION:Fire Truck House
SEQUENCE:0
