BEGIN:VEVENT
CATEGORIES:Lecture/Presentation/Talk,Performance
DESCRIPTION:​The Stanford Doerr School of Sustainability (SDSS)'s Access\, 
 Belonging & Community (ABC) Office invites you to our Lunar New Year Coffee
  Convo on Friday\, February 13 from 11:30–12:30pm in the Hartley Conference
  Room and Mitchell Patio. We'll gather to celebrate\, connect\, and welcome
  the year of the horse together.\n\n​Lunar New Year is one of the most impo
 rtant and widely celebrated holidays across East\, Southeast\, and parts of
  South Asia. Rooted in centuries-old traditions\, it marks the beginning of
  the lunar calendar and is a time for renewal\, family\, gratitude\, and th
 e sharing of good fortune. Across cultures\, Lunar New Year is honored thro
 ugh food\, storytelling\, music\, gifts\, and rituals meant to bring health
 \, prosperity\, and joy in the year ahead.\n\n​We’re excited to have repres
 entation from the Asian American Graduate Student Association and to hear f
 rom Jennifer Lee\, (Graduate Student in the East Asian Studies and Modern T
 hought and Literature Programs) who will share information about the Asian 
 American Activities Center and the work done by staff and students on campu
 s and in the community. \n\n​At 12:00pm\, step outside to the Mitchell Pati
 o for a special performance by the Stanford Lion Dance Club. Founded in 201
 9\, the Stanford Lion Dance Club  is an Asian-American organization dedicat
 ed to spreading good luck\, sharing blessings\, and raising awareness about
  cultural heritage through performance. Lion dance is a vibrant and powerfu
 l tradition often featured during Lunar New Year celebrations\, combining d
 ance\, costumes\, martial arts\, music\, and acting. Originating in China\,
  lion dance has spread across many regions\, including Vietnam\, Korea\, Si
 ngapore\, Malaysia\, and Indonesia\, evolving into many distinct regional s
 tyles. The performance is meant to invite good fortune and positive energy 
 for the year ahead.\n\n​We’ll also be sharing red envelopes\, giving away f
 un prizes\, and serving coffee from Phin Cafe\, a beloved Asian-American-ow
 ned brand.\n\n​Come for the coffee\, and celebrate community\, tradition\, 
 and new beginnings with us. All are welcome. 🧧✨\n\n​Program Itinerary\n\n​1
 1:30-12pm : Coffee Convo Social with red envelopes\, fun prizes and opportu
 nity to learn about the Asian American Graduate Student Association\, the A
 sian American Activities Center and Stanford Lion Dance Club members\n\n​12
 :00-12:05pm: Transition into Mitchell Patio for Stanford Lion Dance Club pe
 rformance \n\n​12:05-12:15pm: Stanford Lion Dance Club Performance\n\n​12:1
 5-12:30pm: Continue with coffee convo social
DTEND:20260213T203000Z
DTSTAMP:20260308T083907Z
DTSTART:20260213T193000Z
GEO:37.426402;-122.172635
LOCATION:Mitchell Earth Sciences\, Hartley Conference Room 
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:Welcoming the Lunar New Year with the Stanford Lion Dance Club 
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_51967040678991
URL:https://events.stanford.edu/event/welcoming-the-lunar-new-year-with-the
 -stanford-lion-dance-club
