BEGIN:VEVENT
CATEGORIES:Class/Seminar
DESCRIPTION:Discover the vibrant flavors and proven health benefits of the 
 Mediterranean way of eating! Known for supporting heart health and longevit
 y\, the Mediterranean diet emphasizes fresh\, plant-based foods\, healthy f
 ats like olive oil\, whole grains\, and lean proteins such as fish and poul
 try—all while keeping red meat and added sugars to a minimum.\n\nIn this en
 gaging virtual cooking demonstration\, you’ll learn how to prepare a simple
  yet delicious meal inspired by the Mediterranean region. As the instructor
  guides you through each step\, you’ll gain practical tips on how to incorp
 orate these nourishing ingredients into your everyday cooking and understan
 d their relation to heart health.\n\nThroughout the class\, the instructor 
 will share easy ingredient swaps and protein options to accommodate a varie
 ty of dietary needs and preferences—so you can tailor each dish to suit you
 r lifestyle.\n\nBy the end of the session\, you’ll walk away with a collect
 ion of wholesome\, flavorful recipes that you and your family will love—and
  your heart will thank you for. A complete recipe packet\, including ingred
 ient lists and equipment notes\, will be provided afterward so you can recr
 eate these Mediterranean-inspired meals in your own kitchen.\n\nThis class 
 will be recorded and a one-week link to the recording will be shared with a
 ll registered participants. To receive incentive points\, attend at least 8
 0% of the live session or listen to the entire recording within one week.  
 Request disability accommodations and access info.\n\nInstructor: Lisa Robe
 rts\, M.Phil.\, is a culinary archaeologist\, chef\, and founder of Lisa Ro
 berts Health\, Nutrition & Lifestyle Advisory. She teaches at Stanford Heal
 thy Living\, NYU\, and Canyon Ranch\, and holds degrees from Oxford\, Tufts
 \, and The French Culinary Institute.\n\nClass details are subject to chang
 e.
DTEND:20260213T210000Z
DTSTAMP:20260308T083907Z
DTSTART:20260213T200000Z
LOCATION:
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:Heart Healthy Mediterranean
