BEGIN:VEVENT
CATEGORIES:Workshop
DESCRIPTION:Participants: RSVP BY FEB 08 | Only 10 Slots available | Open t
 o Stanford Students\n\nObservers: RSVP By FEB 12 | Open to the Stanford Stu
 dents\, Faculty\, and Staff\n\nIn this workshop\, "Working: How to Animate 
 an Idea—Get It Supported\, and to What End\," Anna Deavere Smith explores t
 he vital intersection of creative expression and artistic entrepreneurship.
  The session will move beyond theory into the practicalities of creating an
  artistic project: defining your content\, identifying your purpose\, and s
 trategizing for financial and community support. Open to both participants 
 and observers\, Smith will work with participants on how you move from "hav
 ing an idea" to "securing support" and to "finding an audience."\n\nPartici
 pants and Observers are asked to familiarize themselves with Smith’s piece 
 Notes from the Field\, and if time permits with Letters to a Young Artist. 
  [Links and specifics are sent via email after RSVP.] \n\nParticipants will
  also be asked to submit a short paragraph project proposal that will be se
 nt to Smith ahead of time and you will explore together during the workshop
 .
DTEND:20260214T010000Z
DTSTAMP:20260308T083907Z
DTSTART:20260213T220000Z
GEO:37.426008;-122.174909
LOCATION:Roble Gym\, Harry\, J. Elam\, Jr. Theater
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:WORKSHOP | Anna Deavere Smith
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_51888861536915
