BEGIN:VEVENT
CATEGORIES:Lecture/Presentation/Talk
DESCRIPTION:This lecture\, led by Stanford music faculty Ory Shihor\, explo
 res how performers make informed interpretive decisions when the musical sc
 ore leaves essential elements unspecified. Drawing on Classical-era sources
 \, formal analysis\, and performance practice\, the discussion examines how
  notation\, style\, and context shape choices of articulation\, timing\, ph
 rasing\, and expression. Emphasis is placed on developing interpretive judg
 ment that balances historical awareness with artistic responsibility.\n\nAd
 mission Information\n\nFree admission
