BEGIN:VEVENT
CATEGORIES:Lecture/Presentation/Talk
DESCRIPTION:Pediatric Grand Rounds in Recognition of Black History Month\nA
 dvocacy in Historic Times: Honoring Our Legacy and Forging Our Future\n\nSP
 EAKER\nTerri McFadden\, MD\nPresident Elect\, American Academy of Pediatric
 s\nProfessor\, General Pediatrics\, Emory University School of Medicine\n\n
 SESSION DESCRIPTION\nThis session will discuss the history of advocacy for 
 children and families in the US. Basic tenets of advocacy will be explored 
 as we discuss the AAP's current approach to and priorities for advocacy. Fi
 nally\, we will examine the importance of advocacy in contentious times\, a
 nd describe the benefits of advocacy for both children and advocates.\n\nED
 UCATION GOALS\n\nDefine Advocacy and describe the basic tenets.Discuss the 
 AAP's long history of advocacy for children and families and describe how t
 he past shapes current advocacy priorities.Describe practical steps as well
  as benefits of advocacy during unsettling times.\nZOOM INFORMATION\n[Regis
 ter for Webinar]\n\nSubscribe to receive weekly email announcements and Zoo
 m webinar information for each session.\nSubscribe to mailing list\n\n\nCME
  ACCREDITATION\nThis session is eligible for CME credit. To claim CME credi
 t\, text code to (844) 560-1904 to confirm attendance. A new code will be p
 rovided at beginning of the session.
DTEND:20260217T170000Z
DTSTAMP:20260308T083907Z
DTSTART:20260217T160000Z
GEO:37.437255;-122.171767
LOCATION:Center for Academic Medicine \, Grand Rounds Room 
SEQUENCE:0
