BEGIN:VEVENT
CATEGORIES:Class/Seminar
DESCRIPTION:This class is co-sponsored by the Stanford WorkLife Office.\n\n
 Caring for ourselves and those we love as we age can bring about many quest
 ions about what to expect and hope for as time unfolds.\n\nIn this free web
 inar\, we will provide guidance on forming long term care\, health\, legal\
 , and financial goals for yourself or a care recipient\, and how to build n
 etworks of support to meet your goals. We will discuss the spectrum of care
 \, from non-skilled to skilled care\, and the insurance and financial consi
 derations for each type of care. We will provide resources to guide you as 
 you begin planning\, with checklists and legal explainers to support you al
 ong the way.\n\nThis webinar is part of the Aging Wisely class series\, pro
 viding a compassionate environment to explore your questions and concerns a
 nd help you gain a holistic perspective on how to approach long-term care p
 lanning for yourself or a loved one. Through presentations and online discu
 ssions\, you will learn strategies and tools to help you assess your specif
 ic long-term care needs and explore solutions to common questions related t
 o care planning.\n\nWhether you are a caregiver to others or interested in 
 your own future care\, you will have the opportunity to develop a customize
 d long-term care roadmap supporting you to successfully plan for care\, wit
 h the input\, advice and support of an expert in gerontology.\n\nThis class
  will be recorded and a one-week link to the recording will be shared with 
 all registered participants. To receive incentive points\, attend at least 
 80% of the live session or listen to the entire recording within one week. 
  Request disability accommodations and access info.\n\nInstructor: Paula Wo
 lfson\, LCSW\, ADSW\, is a licensed clinical social worker on staff with Av
 enidas Senior Community Center in Palo Alto. She is an expert in navigating
  health care transitions\, facilitating caregiver support groups and worksh
 ops. Paula has supported the Stanford community for years\, providing elder
  care consultations and critical resources.\n\nClass details are subject to
  change.
DTEND:20260219T203000Z
DTSTAMP:20260308T083907Z
DTSTART:20260219T190000Z
