CATEGORIES:Conference/Symposium
DESCRIPTION:The Department of African and African American Studies (DAAAS) 
 invites students to the 2026 Opportunity Summit!  \n\nOur theme this year i
 s African and African American Studies in Technology and Media: Pathways fo
 r Change!\n\nYou will be part of an interactive workshop where you'll learn
  how to create application materials that get noticed by employers. We'll c
 over:\n\nWhat employers really want and how to respond to their needsEssent
 ial resume components and effective formatting (including applicant trackin
 g system compatibility)How to showcase your experience using strong action 
 verbs and a proven method for writing impactful bullet point descriptionsTa
 iloring strategies that make your application stand outUsing Gen AI respons
 ibly when crafting application materialsCover letter essentials that comple
 ment your resumeThereafter\, you will hear firsthand experiences\, learn ab
 out internships\, jobs and post-graduate pathways and connect with peers an
 d professionals navigating careers in media and technology.\n\nDate: Monday
  February 23\, 6-8pm\n\nDinner and dessert will be provided. \n\nPlease RSV
 P by 12noon Monday February 23.\n\nDon't miss this exciting opportunity to 
 learn more about opportunities in media and technology.
DTSTAMP:20260308T083908Z
