BEGIN:VEVENT
CATEGORIES:Class/Seminar
DESCRIPTION:Co-Sponsored by the Stanford CIO Council Neurodiversity in IT P
 rogram\n\nNeurodiversity is the range of common differences in thinking and
  behavior which we now understand to be normal variations in humans. This i
 ncludes conditions such as autism\, dyslexia\, ADHD\, and others. Neurodive
 rse variations have played a central role in the development of human socie
 ty\, yet neurodiverse people have been historically misunderstood and margi
 nalized as individuals.\n\nJoin us for this free 90-minute online lunch-and
 -learn educational webinar to gain a better understanding of neurodiversity
  and its role in society and within the workplace. In this session\, you wi
 ll gain a basic awareness of neurodiversity\, an understanding of autistic 
 traits with workplace relevance\, and tips for enabling neurodiverse collea
 gues to be effective in the workplace.\n\nWe will discuss how leading compa
 nies foster neurodiversity to their advantage\, how increasing understandin
 g and acceptance of neuro differences is allowing more people to enter the 
 workplace\, and what concrete steps each of us can take to better understan
 d and support neurodiverse colleagues.\n\nThis class will not be recorded. 
 Attendance requirement for incentive points - at least 80% of the live sess
 ion.  Request disability accommodations and access info.\n\nInstructors: Ra
 nga Jayaraman is the director of Neurodiversity Pathways\, a group of profe
 ssionals bound by the common passion to make a difference in the employment
  outcomes for neurodiverse adults.\n\nJohn Marble is the founder of Pivot N
 eurodiversity and is a writer and speaker on innovation\, autism\, and neur
 odiversity. Whether he’s working in warehouses or inside the White House\, 
 he explores how we can improve systems in order to create better products\,
  policies\, and outcomes.\n\nKhushboo Chabria is a program manager at Neuro
 diversity Pathways. She is a neurodiversity specialist and aims to make a m
 eaningful impact in the world through education\, empowerment\, authentic e
 ngagement\, and unbridled compassion.\n\nThe three instructors are coauthor
 s of the books Neurodiversity for Dummies and Autism for Dummies.\n\nClass 
 details are subject to change.
DTEND:20260224T213000Z
DTSTAMP:20260308T083908Z
DTSTART:20260224T200000Z
LOCATION:
