CATEGORIES:Lecture/Presentation/Talk
DESCRIPTION:Come learn more about the western snowy plover\, a diminutive s
 horebird that calls the beaches of Monterey Bay home. Point Blue Conservati
 on Science ecologist Kriss Neuman has spent decades studying this tiny\, th
 reatened shorebird and will share information on the plover’s life history 
 and breeding ecology\, discuss why California’s sandy beaches are so import
 ant to the survival of this species\, and the threats they face\, including
  from climate and habitat change.\n\nRegistration required whether attendin
 g in person or via Zoom.\n\nZoom Registration Link\n\nIn-Person Registratio
 n Link
