BEGIN:VEVENT
CATEGORIES:Lecture/Presentation/Talk
DESCRIPTION:Seema Kohli is one of India’s most distinguished contemporary a
 rtists\, with a practice that spans painting\, drawing\, sculpture\, instal
 lation\, and performance. For more than four decades\, her work has brought
  together memory\, mythology\, spirituality\, and lived experience\, creati
 ng immersive environments that invite reflection and contemplation.\nKohli'
 s work has been featured in major international exhibitions and museums\, i
 ncluding a solo exhibition at the Museum of Sacred Art in Belgium in 2019 a
 nd the Kochi-Muziris Biennale in 2016. Her work is held in institutional co
 llections such as the British Museum (UK)\, Rubin Museum (USA)\, and the Bi
 ll and Melinda Gates Foundation (US)\, among others.\nKohli is also a sough
 t-after speaker and has been invited to present at organizations and instit
 utions including TEDx\, Harvard University\, the University of Chicago\, an
 d the University of California at Davis\, among others.\n\nAbout the talk\n
 In this reflective talk\, artist Seema Kohli will share personal insights o
 n self-discovery\, being true to one’s self\, and the transformative power 
 of deep inner work. Through art and lived experience\, she explores how red
 esigning the self from within can renew both body and mind. She will lead t
 he audience through her journey with an immersive animated projection that 
 gradually reveals her art. This talk invites listeners into a contemplative
  space\, offering art and poetry as a guide for inner transformation.\n\nLe
 arn more about Seema Kohli's work and check out her special exhibition: Sam
 sara & Metamorphosis: The Mystical World of Seema Kohli" with LAASYA Art  a
 t the Pacific Art League.
DTEND:20260225T040000Z
DTSTAMP:20260308T083908Z
DTSTART:20260225T030000Z
GEO:37.426792;-122.164842
LOCATION:Encina Commons\, 123
SEQUENCE:0
