BEGIN:VEVENT
CATEGORIES:PhD Defense
DESCRIPTION:Title: Informing Water and Nutrient Management for Sustainable 
 Agriculture\n\nAbstract:\n\nEffective management of water and nutrient reso
 urces remains a central challenge for sustainable agricultural production. 
 Agronomic decisions and how they impact crop yields and other relevant outc
 omes\, such as consumptive water use\, are highly field specific. Variabili
 ty over space and time for both meteorological and management factors also 
 makes it difficult to identify how specific agricultural practices\, often 
 funded through grant programs\, impact outcomes of interest. The research i
 n this dissertation investigates how high-resolution satellite data product
 s\, combined with field-level agronomic analyses\, can guide the implementa
 tion of agricultural management programs\, strategies\, and technologies.\n
 \nDespite substantial and continued investments into agri-environmental pro
 grams\, systematic evaluation remains limited\, making it essential to quan
 tify their effectiveness and ensure that expected outcomes are being achiev
 ed. High-resolution spatial analysis across large regions can also identify
  where technologies\, agri-environmental practices\, or subsidy programs ar
 e likely to be the most effective and have the greatest potential. This res
 earch proposes several frameworks that facilitate informed decision-making 
 at multiple scales\, identify opportunities for targeted improvement\, and 
 guide future research efforts that support sustainable agricultural managem
 ent.
DTEND:20260225T223000Z
DTSTAMP:20260308T083908Z
DTSTART:20260225T213000Z
GEO:37.42816;-122.175935
LOCATION:Y2E2 Building\, 299
