CATEGORIES:Exhibition
DESCRIPTION:This exhibit showcases capstone projects from "The Senior Refle
 ction" in the Biology Department\, a unique course that asks students to co
 nceive\, produce\, and exhibit a creative project centering around Biology 
 or the life sciences.\n\nCo-founded and taught by Professor Susan McConnell
  and Lecturer Andrew Todhunter\, the course provides a space for students t
 o blend their scientific studies with creative expression\, using media as 
 diverse as painting\, poetry\, needle point\, bookmaking\, and the performi
 ng arts. The projects in this display were created by students in the 2024-
 2025 cohort. \n\nThe exhibit will be on display in Hohbach Hall in Green Li
 brary for the duration of the Winter 2026 quarter.
