BEGIN:VEVENT
CATEGORIES:Workshop
DESCRIPTION:Abstraction as Agency: Salt and Resist Watercolor Painting with
  Rachelle Reichert invites participants to explore Alteronce Gumby’s painti
 ngs through the lens of material agency and the cosmos. Led by local artist
  Rachelle Reichert\, the workshop considers raw materials as active collabo
 rators in the art-making process. Participants will experiment with salt an
 d resist watercolor techniques to create their own vibrant\, process-based 
 paintings.\n\nThe workshop is open to Stanford Students only. If you are a 
 member of the public or Stanford Community\, please RSVP for this session.\
 n\nRSVP Here! \n\nRachelle Reichert is a visual artist whose work explores 
 the intersections of environment\, history\, and the global economy through
  terrestrial materials. Working with harvested salt and earth\, she creates
  multimedia works that consider landscape as a living record of human prese
 nce and geological time. Her geometric forms draw on lunar symbology and sa
 lt crystallization\, creating a dialogue between the celestial and the terr
 estrial. Reichert’s work has been exhibited at major institutions including
  the Autry (Getty PST)\, the Contemporary Jewish Museum\, and the Center fo
 r Contemporary Art at PNCA. Her research is archived at the Nevada Museum o
 f Art’s Center for Art + Environment and SFMOMA\, and her work is held in c
 orporate collections such as Google and Meta\, with coverage in Architectur
 al Digest\, the San Francisco Chronicle\, and New American Paintings.
DTEND:20260301T213000Z
DTSTAMP:20260308T083909Z
DTSTART:20260301T193000Z
GEO:37.433768;-122.170791
LOCATION:Anderson Collection
SEQUENCE:0
