BEGIN:VEVENT
CATEGORIES:Exhibition,Social Event/Reception
DESCRIPTION:Join Conservation Services from Stanford University Libraries f
 or a pop-up exhibition and open house featuring conservation work on materi
 als from Special Collections. A variety of materials from medieval manuscri
 pts to bespoke protective enclosures will be on display\, and Conservation 
 staff will be around to talk about their roles in keeping the library's phy
 sical collection in usable condition for future generations of Stanford stu
 dents\, faculty\, and researchers.\n\nConservation Services staff care for 
 rare and unique materials from Special Collections and Locked Stacks\, with
  core expertise in paper-based collections including books\, manuscripts\, 
 unbound items like maps and posters. Conservation staff also provide guidan
 ce on photographs\, objects\, and the full spectrum of materials found in a
 n archival collection. In a typical year\, Conservation staff complete appr
 oximately 700 treatments and produce over 1\,100 storage enclosures. Their 
 work draws on experience  with a wide variety of materials in varying condi
 tions as well as a strong understanding of how things have been made across
  centuries to ensure long-term preservation and accessibility of SUL collec
 tions.\n\nDrop by Hobach Hall 123 (Silicon Valley Archive classroom\, Green
  Library) anytime between 2-4pm on Monday\, March 2nd to chat with conserva
 tion staff and see how conservation work impacts Special Collections materi
 als.
DTEND:20260303T000000Z
