BEGIN:VEVENT
CATEGORIES:Meeting,Workshop,Other
DESCRIPTION:Sign-Up for our FREE Naloxone Trainings facilitated by PEERs an
 d in collaboration with the Well House. \n\nWhat is Naloxone (NARCAN)?\n\nN
 ALOXONE is a potentially lifesaving medication designed to help reverse the
  effects of an opioid overdose in minutes. Since most opioid overdoses occu
 r in the home and are most often witnessed\, having a NALOXONE rescue kit n
 earby can make all the difference. Upon completing the training\, you will 
 be able to leave with your own box of Free Naloxone. You can find our list 
 of workshop dates below:\n\nMonday\, March 2\, 2025 (7-8pm)If you want to r
 equest another time and location for my group/organization please fill out 
 this interest form.RSVP Here! Drop-ins are also welcome but RSVP helps us k
 now how much Naloxone to bring.\n\nFree naloxone will be provided for atten
 dees following the training.Drop ins welcome!Open to ALL Stanford Affiliate
 s (students\, faculty\, staff\, etc.) Learn more about the Opioid Epidemic 
 and walk away with the ability to save a life!\n\nIf you have any questions
  about this event or want to request a Naloxone training please contact us 
 at peerprogram@stanford.edu
DTEND:20260303T040000Z
DTSTAMP:20260308T083909Z
DTSTART:20260303T030000Z
GEO:37.421896;-122.169177
LOCATION: The Well House\, Lobby 562 Mayfield Ave\, Stanford\, CA 94305\, T
 he Well House\, Lobby
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:FREE Naloxone (Narcan) Training
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_51499764891987
URL:https://events.stanford.edu/event/free-naloxone-narcan-training-1593
