DESCRIPTION:Co-Hosted with the Stanford Program in Data Science & Social Sy
 stems.\n\nWho creates the maps?  How?  And\, what is at stake?  \n\nLong be
 fore billions can be invested in clean energy projects\, a multi-agency pro
 cess for Long Range Planning shapes the landscape of opportunity for new re
 sources - and the prospects for retiring old ones.\n\nEmily Leslie is the f
 ounder of Montara Mountain Energy and is a Stanford alumna who also teaches
  in Spring Quarter the course called Spatial Planning for Gigascale Renewab
 les & Transmission (CEE 176M / 276M). She is an expert in scenario analysis
  and maps inform decisions at ​the largest scale in California's energy eco
 nomy. This is your chance to gain a more vivid perspective on how that work
 s\, and what it means. \n\nEmcee:  Explore Energy Peer Advisor and ace in s
 patial planning for giga-scale renewables and transmission\, Ariana Carmody
