BEGIN:VEVENT
CATEGORIES:Film/Screening
DESCRIPTION:Please join us for the screening of "Animals in War" and Q&A wi
 th the producer Adam Sigel (on zoom). WHEN: March 3\, 6 p.m.WHERE: Pigott H
 all (Bldg. 260)\, Rm. 113 "Animals in War" (2025) is a unique Ukrainian ant
 hology film based on true stories of animals affected by the war in Ukraine
 . The main characters of its seven novellas are animals that found themselv
 es in the midst of war—among them a white rabbit\, a wolf\, and a cow. This
  project sheds light on the humanitarian and ecological catastrophe caused 
 by war\, portraying it through the perspective of animals who are powerless
  against its consequences. The film was created in collaboration with both 
 Ukrainian and international artists\, including Hollywood actor\, director\
 , and producer Sean Penn\, who\, for the first time in the history of Ukrai
 nian cinema\, became part of a domestic film.Directors: Yulia Shashkova\, S
 viatoslav Kostiuk\, Andrii Lidahovskyi\, Maksym Tuzov\, Alexei Mamedov\, My
 roslav SlaboshpytskyiProducers: Oleg Kokhan\, Oleksiy Makukhin
DTEND:20260304T030000Z
DTSTAMP:20260308T083909Z
DTSTART:20260304T020000Z
