DESCRIPTION:This 6-session support group\, co-facilitated by two MHT clinic
 ians\, offers a student-centered space to show up as you are\, connect with
  peers\, and build community.\n\nTogether we’ll explore ways to navigate ac
 ademic and professional stress\, manage anxiety\, reflect on identity-relat
 ed experiences\, and address impostor feelings- along with other student-le
 d topics. The group also fosters moments of joy and connection as part of t
 he healing process.\n\nThis group is held on Thursdays 8:30-9:30 AM\, start
 ing January 22\, 2026. Meeting dates for winter quarter are 1/22\; 1/29\; 2
 /5\; 2/12\; 2/26\; 3/5. Sessions are both virtual and in-person.  In-person
  dates are 1/29\; 2/12\; 3/5.\n\nA meeting with a facilitator is required t
 o join this group. You can sign up on the on "*INTEREST_LIST_SOM_Students_o
 f_Color_GROUP_WINTER_Q" on the Vaden Portal rosters\, in the "Groups and Wo
 rkshops" section. A facilitator will reach out to you to schedule a pre-gro
 up meeting.\n\nOpen to all registered BioSci PhD/MS\, MSPA\, and MD student
 s in the School of Medicine.Facilitated by Isela Garcia White\, LCSW and Ma
 riko Sweetnam\, LCSW
