DESCRIPTION:The Molecular Imaging Program at Stanford (MIPS) was establishe
 d as an inter-disciplinary program in 2003 by the Dean of the School of Med
 icine (Dr. Philip Pizzo) and brings together scientists and physicians who 
 share a common interest in developing and using state-of-the-art imaging te
 chnology and developing molecular imaging assays for studying intact biolog
 ical systems. The inaugural director was Dr. Sanjiv Sam Gambhir\, Virginia 
 & D.K. Ludwig Professor of Cancer Research and Chair of the Department of R
 adiology from 2003 to 2020. MIPS hosts a seminar series that is open and fr
 ee to everyone in the Stanford community. Our next seminar will host Peder 
 Larson\, PhD\, for a presentation titled\, “Cardiopulmonary MRI in Two Part
 s: Metabolic Imaging in the Heart with Hyperpolarized 13C MRI\, and Methods
  for MRI in the Lungs.”\n\n \n\nLocation: Zoom & Clark\, S360\nZoom Webinar
  Details\nWebinar URL: https://stanford.zoom.us/s/92078802008\nDial US: +1 
 650 724 9799 or +1 833 302 1536\nWebinar ID: 920 7880 2008\nPasscode: 23680
 6\n\n \n\nHosted by: Michelle James\, PhD\nSponsored by: Molecular Imaging 
 Program at Stanford & the Department of Radiology
