BEGIN:VEVENT
CATEGORIES:Class/Seminar,Conference/Symposium,Lecture/Presentation/Talk
DESCRIPTION:“Communication for Action: Doing It and Doing It Socially”\n\nT
 his talk will begin with the premise that even though humans evolved for ac
 tion and social coordination\, communication programs are often dissociated
  from these principles. I will describe experiments to determine whether an
 d how to promote action through the introduction of explicit or implicit be
 havioral information\, recommendations to perform rather than not perform a
  behavior\, and directions to start rather than stop a behavior. I will the
 n show how artificial intelligence can be used to optimize action-oriented 
 communications aligned with these principles\, concluding with the results 
 of a large-scale randomized controlled trial in underserved areas of the Un
 ited States.\n\nBiography\n\nDolores Albarracín studies the impact of commu
 nication and persuasion on human behavior and the formation of beliefs\, at
 titudes\, and goals\, particularly those that are socially beneficial. In a
 ddition to an interest in basic attitudinal processes\, she is interested i
 n finding ways of intervening to promote positive social interactions and p
 ublic policies.
DTEND:20260305T223000Z
DTSTAMP:20260308T083909Z
DTSTART:20260305T211500Z
GEO:37.42816;-122.175935
LOCATION:Y2E2 Building\, 300
