BEGIN:VEVENT
CATEGORIES:Lecture/Presentation/Talk
DESCRIPTION:In an era defined by political friction and social fragmentatio
 n\, how do we move from "us vs. them" to  "we"? Join  the Palo Alto Library
  and Silicon Valley Reads for an insightful evening at Stanford’s Hauck Aud
 itorium as part of Silicon Valley Reads\, Bridges to Belonging.\n\nWorld-re
 nowned social psychologist Dr. Jennifer Eberhardt (Biased: Uncovering the H
 idden Prejudice That Shapes What We See\, Think\, and Do) joins visionary l
 egal scholar john a. powell ( The Power of Bridging: How to Build a World W
 here we all Belong) to explore the roots of implicit bias and the architect
 ure of "othering."  Join us to learn how  to soothe tensions\, bridge divid
 es\, and foster a sense of belonging in a complex world.\n\njohn a. powell 
 is Director of the Othering and Belonging Institute and Professor of Law\, 
 African American\, and Ethnic Studies at the University of California\, Ber
 keley.\n\nA social psychologist at Stanford University\, Jennifer L. Eberha
 rdt conducts research on race and inequality. She not only highlights the n
 egative impact that racial bias can have on us in these settings — she prov
 ides clear direction on what we can do about it. \n\nThis event is in partn
 ership with the Palo Alto City Library and Stanford University.\n\nBooks wi
 ll be available for sale from 6:00pm with a book signing opportunity at the
  end of the event.\n\nRegistration is recommended to receive event updates 
 and venue/parking directions.\n\nREGISTER HERE
DTEND:20260306T034500Z
DTSTAMP:20260308T083909Z
