DESCRIPTION:The Stanford Sustainability Accelerator\, the Center for Sustai
 nability Data Science\, and the Institute for Human-Centered Artificial Int
 elligence invite you to join our Data Science for Sustainability series. Th
 is session is a Lunch & Learn on Computer Vision for Sustainability.\n\nThi
 s session will cover:\n\nCore computer vision methods and emerging approach
 es (e.g.\, image segmentation\, object detection\, foundation models)Applic
 ations across climate adaptation\, energy systems\, agriculture\, urban res
 ilience\, conservation\, and moreOpportunities for cross-disciplinary colla
 boration\n Why this matters: Many sustainability challenges depend on extra
 cting insights from visual data at scale—from monitoring ecosystem change t
 o assessing climate risk. This session will explore how advances in compute
 r vision are expanding what we can measure\, validate\, and act on\, and ma
 y offer relevant tools and collaborations for your own research.\n\n \n\nDa
 te: March 6th\, 2026\n\nTime: 12:00 PM - 1:30 PM\n\nLocation: CoDa E160
