BEGIN:VEVENT
CATEGORIES:PhD Defense
DESCRIPTION:Geophysics has entered an era of rapidly expanding data availab
 ility across a wide range of spatial scales. During my PhD journey\, I have
  explored data-driven approaches to tackle geophysical challenges at each s
 cale\, from pore to regional levels. Pore scale (∼10-6 m): High-resolution 
 image dataChapter 2: GNN for effective elastic moduli prediction.Chapter 3:
  Diffusion-based multiphase flow generation given fracture geometries.Chapt
 er 4: Image registration of a thin section in a CT image (In revision for G
 eophysics)Decameter scale (∼10 m): EGS Collab hydraulic stimulation and mic
 roearthquake history dataChapter 5: Forecasting fluid-induced microearthqua
 kesRegional scale (∼105 m): Machine learning and routine-based seismicity c
 atalog dataChapter 6: Quantifying spatial detectability of a machine-learni
 ng-based seismicity catalog (Accepted/In press for Seismological Research L
 etters) Given the limited time\, the public defense presentation will prima
 rily focus on one study at each scale: Chapters 2\, 5\, and 6.
DTEND:20260306T230000Z
