BEGIN:VEVENT
CATEGORIES:Performance
DESCRIPTION:The acclaimed Stanford Afro-Latin Jazz Ensemble\, directed by M
 urray Low\, presents their Winter Concert titled "Tribute to the Mambo" fea
 turing special guest saxophonist/flautist Mitch Frohman.  The program showc
 ases both classic and original repertoire paying homage to classic New York
  Salsa and Latin Jazz repertoire during its golden era.\n\nA seven-time Gra
 mmy winner\, Mr. Frohman literally "lived" the New York Salsa/Latin Jazz sc
 ene through his 25-year stint as a key member of the legendary Tito Puente 
 Orchestra as also as part of the Mongo Santamaria band for many years.   He
  is now a bandleader in his own right as a founder of the Mambo Legends Orc
 hestra and as a leader of his own Latin Jazz Quartet\, which released a cri
 tically acclaimed CD "From Daddy With Love".\n\nMr. Frohman is internationa
 lly recognized as a pioneer in the idiom\, having been awarded Latin Jazz U
 SA's Lifetime Achievement Award in 2016.  He has collaborated with all of t
 he greats - Celia Cruz\, Joe Cuba\, Chico O'Farrill\, Machito\, Eddie Palmi
 eri\, and the Spanish Harlem Orchestra - to name just a few!  You've probab
 ly heard his signature sound on commercial recordings also\, such as the th
 eme song from Sex In The City\, or songs performed by Paul Simon\, the Talk
 ing Heads\, and Cyndi Lauper.\n\nDon't miss this special chance to hear thi
 s legendary music directly from the source!   .\n\nAdmission Information\n\
 nGeneral – $32 | Seniors (65+) and Non-Stanford Students – $27\nPrice shown
  reflects total cost including $4 online/phone per-ticket fee.FREE admissio
 n for Stanford University students. One ticket per ID\, available beginning
  one hour prior to curtain at the venue.This event will be livestreamed.
DTEND:20260308T050000Z
DTSTAMP:20260308T083910Z
DTSTART:20260308T033000Z
