CATEGORIES:Conference/Symposium,Film/Screening
DESCRIPTION:The William & Louise Greaves Filmmaker Seminar is a gathering d
 edicated to artists working in cinematic realms. Hosted by BlackStar in par
 tnership with Stanford University’s Institute for Diversity in the Arts\, t
 his seminar provides an immersive space where filmmakers\, curators\, schol
 ars\, critics\, and cultural workers can explore both the technical and cre
 ative dimensions of media-making.\n\nNamed after William and Louise Greaves
 \, visionary documentarians whose work broke new ground in truth-telling an
 d representation the seminar is built around honest conversations: success\
 , struggle\, craft\, theory\, innovation\, and community!
