CATEGORIES:Exhibition
DESCRIPTION:In honor of Women’s History Month\, we are proud to unveil our 
 latest book exhibit: "Women in Science." Located in the Li & Ma Science Lib
 rary\, this collection celebrates the women scientists\, researchers\, and 
 innovators who have transformed our world.\n\nFrom the laboratory to the fi
 eld\, these titles highlight the diverse and often under-told stories of wo
 men who pioneered new frontiers in STEM.\n\nExhibit Highlights\n\nStop by t
 o browse our curated selection\, featuring:\n\nMemoirs of Discovery: Dive i
 nto the personal journeys of scientists like Hope Jahren in Lab Girl or Dia
 ne Boyd’s experiences in A Woman Among Wolves.\n\nGlobal Perspectives: Expl
 ore international contributions with titles such as Japanese Women in Scien
 ce and Engineering and Women in Global Science.\n\nHidden Histories: Learn 
 about the foundational work of African American chemists and the "Immortal 
 Life" of Henrietta Lacks.\n\nCareer & Culture: Examine the modern landscape
  of the field through books like Women in STEM Careers and Every Other Thur
 sday.
DTEND:20260311T000000Z
