BEGIN:VEVENT
CATEGORIES:Workshop
DESCRIPTION:Please join us for a workshop with Junior Professor Margit Dahm
  (Kiel University) entitled\, "Female Writers\, Female Writing: Markings of
  Female Textual Production in German-Language Manuscripts"\n\nThe workshop 
 addresses the question of female participation in medieval writing\, which 
 is explored on the basis of an evaluation of scribal colophons from German-
 language manuscripts of the Middle Ages. After outlining what information v
 alue colophons provide about medieval scribes\, the workshop adresses the q
 uestion of gender-specific information. How did female scribes articulate t
 hemselves in a male-dominated writing tradition? What specific strategies h
 ave they used to mark the manuscripts for which they were responsible? What
  conclusions can be drawn from these observations about female professional
 ism in medieval writing?\n\nThe lecture will be followed by a joint reading
  and discussion of selected colophons written by female writers. By examini
 ng these texts for signs of female writing and gender-specific forms of col
 ophon design\, the traces of female agency in medieval writing are investig
 ated.\n\nRSVP for the Margit Dahm Workshop
DTEND:20260310T203000Z
DTSTAMP:20260308T083910Z
DTSTART:20260310T190000Z
GEO:37.427405;-122.1697
LOCATION:Building 260\, Pigott Hall\, Rm 252
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:SCRIPTA: JProf. Margit Dahm: Female Writers\, Female Writing: Marki
 ngs of Female Textual Production in German-Language Manuscripts
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_52056585068463
URL:https://events.stanford.edu/event/scripta-jprof-margit-dahm-female-writ
 ers-female-writing-markings-of-female-textual-production-in-german-language
