BEGIN:VEVENT
CATEGORIES:Exhibition
DESCRIPTION:Branner Earth Sciences Library & Map Collection exhibit series:
  Oceans\n\nIn the 2025–2026 academic year\, Branner Library’s exhibit serie
 s will explore Earth’s oceans’ complex biological and ecological systems th
 at regulate climate and support life.\n\nMarch’s exhibition explores how th
 e physical properties of seawater\, large-scale circulation systems\, and d
 ynamic air–sea exchanges regulate Earth’s climate system\, redistribute hea
 t and carbon across the globe\, and inform pressing environmental and socie
 tal questions in an era of accelerating change.\n\nThe exhibition features 
 print books\, maps\, and e-resources\, providing a range of resources for u
 ndergraduate and graduate students\, as well as specialists working in the 
 field of ocean physics.\n\nThe exhibit is available for viewing Monday thro
 ugh Friday during regular library open hours. \nCheck out past exhibits and
  subscribe to the Branner Library Newsletter.  \n\nA current Stanford ID is
  needed to enter the library\, visitors must present a valid\, physical gov
 ernment-issued photo ID to sign-in at the front desk.
