BEGIN:VEVENT
CATEGORIES:Class/Seminar
DESCRIPTION:Co-sponsored by Stanford Residential and Dining Enterprises\n\n
 Eating a diet rich in fiber is crucial for maintaining overall health and w
 ell-being. Fiber prevents constipation\, lowers cholesterol levels\, reduce
 s the risk of heart disease\, helps control blood sugar levels\, supports a
  healthy gut microbiome\, and more. Fortunately\, incorporating a fiber-ric
 h diet is easier and more delicious than you may realize!\n\nJoin us for a 
 hands-on cooking class to learn simple and tasty ways to incorporate more f
 iber into your meals. In this two-hour in-person class\, you will discover 
 how to create a healthy microbiome by getting more than 30 different types 
 of high-fiber foods a week through satiating meals.\n\nWe will explore ferm
 entation techniques\, planning your snacks\, using a pressure cooker for be
 ans and whole grains\, creating a savory teff-buckwheat porridge\, and more
 . You will leave the session with tasty samples to take home and enjoy\, as
  well as a toolbox of strategies to bring more fiber into your daily meals.
 \n\nThe class will take place on campus in the beautiful RD&E teaching kitc
 hen at the Escondido Village Graduate Residences. Due to limited capacity\,
  this class will be capped at 16 participants\, so register soon to secure 
 your spot.\n\nThis is an in-person class and will not be recorded. Attendan
 ce at the live session is required to receive incentive points.  Request di
 sability accommodations and access info.\n\nClass details are subject to ch
 ange.
DTEND:20260318T020000Z
DTSTAMP:20260308T083911Z
