BEGIN:VEVENT
CATEGORIES:Conference/Symposium
DESCRIPTION:Please join us for the 2026 Water in the West Research Conferen
 ce at Stanford University\, hosted by Water in the West (WitW)\, a program 
 of the Stanford Woods Institute for the Environment and the Bill Lane Cente
 r for the American West.\n\nThis conference will examine issues of critical
  importance to water resources in the western U.S. and the world at large. 
  Leading faculty and researchers from Stanford and other universities acros
 s the West will present innovative research on water equity and affordabili
 ty\, environmental protection\, sustainable urban water systems\, effective
  groundwater management\, water information systems\, interjurisdictional w
 ater governance\, Native American water rights\, adaptation to climate chan
 ge and droughts\, and other major water challenges.  In addition to highlig
 hting current research\, the conference will include a roundtable discussio
 n of new and cutting edge research topics.  The conference will provide the
  western water community with an opportunity to connect\, exchange ideas on
  critical topics\, showcase emerging research\, and map future research pro
 jects. We hope you will join us at Stanford on March 17 and 18.\n\nRegister
  | Speakers |Agenda
DTEND:20260318T200000Z
