BEGIN:VEVENT
CATEGORIES:Lecture/Presentation/Talk
DESCRIPTION:Religious diversity is a defining feature of contemporary Ameri
 can democracy\, yet it raises persistent questions about how civic unity is
  cultivated in shared public life. How can institutions of higher education
  prepare students to engage constructively across religious difference whil
 e sustaining common democratic commitments? This webinar explores the role 
 of civic education in a religiously diverse democracy\, examining pedagogic
 al approaches\, institutional frameworks\, and normative principles that su
 pport civic unity without erasing pluralism.\n\nThe Alliance for Civics in 
 the Academy hosts "Building Civic Unity in a Religiously Diverse Democracy"
  with Eboo Patel\, Robert George\, Fr. Francisco Nahoe\, and Josh Ober on M
 arch 18\, 2026\, from 9:00-10:00 a.m. PT.\n\nThe Civics in the Academy webi
 nar series features in-depth discussions on the practice\, pedagogy\, and s
 tate of civics in higher education. Drawing on the diverse expertise and pe
 rspectives within the Alliance network\, each session features topics and p
 anelists sourced directly from our membership. The series aims to foster di
 alogue\, share practical knowledge and best practices\, and contribute to a
  shared\, pluralistic framework in the evolving field of civics in the acad
 emy.
DTEND:20260318T170000Z
DTSTAMP:20260308T083911Z
DTSTART:20260318T160000Z
LOCATION:
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:Building Civic Unity in a Religiously Diverse Democracy
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_52252949457482
URL:https://events.stanford.edu/event/building-civic-unity-in-a-religiously
 -diverse-democracy
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
CATEGORIES:Exhibition
DESCRIPTION:In honor of Women’s History Month\, we are proud to unveil our 
 latest book exhibit: "Women in Science." Located in the Li & Ma Science Lib
 rary\, this collection celebrates the women scientists\, researchers\, and 
 innovators who have transformed our world.\n\nFrom the laboratory to the fi
 eld\, these titles highlight the diverse and often under-told stories of wo
 men who pioneered new frontiers in STEM.\n\nExhibit Highlights\n\nStop by t
 o browse our curated selection\, featuring:\n\nMemoirs of Discovery: Dive i
 nto the personal journeys of scientists like Hope Jahren in Lab Girl or Dia
 ne Boyd’s experiences in A Woman Among Wolves.\n\nGlobal Perspectives: Expl
 ore international contributions with titles such as Japanese Women in Scien
 ce and Engineering and Women in Global Science.\n\nHidden Histories: Learn 
 about the foundational work of African American chemists and the "Immortal 
 Life" of Henrietta Lacks.\n\nCareer & Culture: Examine the modern landscape
  of the field through books like Women in STEM Careers and Every Other Thur
 sday.
DTEND:20260319T000000Z
DTSTAMP:20260308T083911Z
