BEGIN:VEVENT
CATEGORIES:Lecture/Presentation/Talk
DESCRIPTION:Join the Hoover Institution for a special live taping of Firing
  Line with Margaret Hoover\, part of The Ideas That Made U.S.: Dialogues on
  Freedom\, our year-long series marking America’s 250th anniversary.\n\nMar
 garet Hoover will moderate a conversation with General Jim Mattis\, former 
 U.S. Secretary of Defense\, and Ryan Holiday\, bestselling author and moder
 n interpreter of Stoic philosophy\, on the character that sustains a republ
 ic. Drawing on experience in military command\, classical philosophy\, and 
 the enduring example of America’s founding generation\, the discussion will
  explore the virtues that have defined American leadership at its best: dis
 cipline\, moral courage\, humility in the exercise of power\, and a profoun
 d sense of duty.
DTEND:20260319T020000Z
DTSTAMP:20260308T083911Z
