BEGIN:VEVENT
CATEGORIES:Lecture/Presentation/Talk
DESCRIPTION:Join the Blue Food Futures Program to explore how blue foods — 
 fish\, shellfish\, algae\, and other aquatic species harvested from oceans\
 , rivers\, and lakes  — can help build healthy\, equitable\, and sustainabl
 e food systems.\n\nHeld on the Stanford campus\, this session is an opportu
 nity to learn about the latest frontiers in blue food research\, connect wi
 th leading experts\, and network with a global community of blue food schol
 ars committed to driving food system transformation.\n\nThis event is co-or
 ganized by the Stanford Center for Ocean Solutions\, the program's co-found
 er and host of its Secretariat. \n\n9 to 10 am: An opening keynote presente
 d by Professor Jim Leape will provide an overview of the Blue Food Futures 
 Program and highlight the critical role of science and policy in transformi
 ng food systems\, followed by lightning talks from Blue Food Futures Fellow
 s.\n\n10 to 10:30 am: A networking session will follow with coffee and refr
 eshments.\n\nPlease rsvp to bluefoodfutures@stanford.edu if you plan to att
 end one or both portions of the session so we can plan seating and refreshm
 ents accordingly.\n\n \n\n_________________________________________________
 ___________________________________________________________________________
 _____________________________\n\nBlue Food Futures is an endorsed program o
 f the UN Ocean Decade of Ocean Science for Sustainable Development. The pro
 gram strengthens blue food science\, policy\, and community\, and is a coll
 aboration between the Stanford Center for Ocean Solutions\, Stockholm Resil
 ience Centre at Stockholm University\, Environmental Defense Fund\, Governm
 ent of Iceland\, WorldFish\, National Center for Ecological Analysis and Sy
 nthesis\, University of British Columbia\, and Xiamen University.
DTEND:20260319T173000Z
DTSTAMP:20260308T083911Z
