DESCRIPTION:The 2026 Stanford Cancer Institute Research Conference (formerl
 y the Stanford Cancer Institute Retreat) is a scientific event that is desi
 gned to connect Stanford Cancer Institute members\, staff\, and trainees\, 
 as well as the broader Stanford community\, to share innovations in Stanfor
 d cancer research and foster meaningful collaboration.\n\nJoin us Tuesday\,
  March 24\, 2026\, at Berg Hall\, Li Ka Shing Center\, to engage in scienti
 fic talks\, breakout sessions\, poster presentations\, and an annual update
  from Steven Artandi\, MD\, PhD\, director of the Stanford Cancer Institute
 . Following the conference\, a reception will allow both familiar faces and
  new colleagues to connect\, exchange ideas\, and strengthen collaborations
 . \n\nThe event is open to Stanford Cancer Institute members\, postdocs\, f
 ellows\, residents\, and students\, as well as Stanford University and Stan
 ford Medicine faculty\, trainees\, and staff.\n\nRegistration is encouraged
 .\n\nPoster Session\n\nStanford Cancer Institute members\, students\, postd
 ocs\, residents\, fellows\, and staff are invited to participate in the pos
 ter sessions. Submit your abstract through the registration form by March 1
 6 to showcase your research to Stanford faculty.
