BEGIN:VEVENT
CATEGORIES:Workshop
DESCRIPTION:Join us for our March Manager Forums as Dr. Meghan Imrie\, MD\,
  Clinical Assistant Professor of Orthopaedic Surgery\, leads a powerful con
 versation on what may be the most overlooked lever of leadership: behavior.
  \n\n \n\nIn high-stakes environments like orthopedic surgery training\, te
 chnical excellence is expected. But what truly determines trust\, professio
 nalism and team culture are the non-technical skills: the behaviors leaders
  model and reinforce. \n\n \n\nDr. Imrie will challenge us to examine: \n\n
 What specific behaviors earn and maintain the public’s trust Whether profes
 sionalism can truly be taught\, or simply selected for  \n\nThe central que
 stion: Can (and should) we own the B?\n\n \n\nWhether you lead in a clinic\
 , lab\, classroom\, or campus office\, this session will push you to reflec
 t on how behavior ultimately defines your team’s culture.If you care about 
 accountability\, credibility\, and the standards you want your team to live
  by\, this conversation is for you.\n\n \n\nJoin us for what promises to be
  a candid and thought-provoking session.
DTEND:20260325T180000Z
DTSTAMP:20260308T083911Z
DTSTART:20260325T170000Z
LOCATION:
