BEGIN:VEVENT
CATEGORIES:Class/Seminar
DESCRIPTION:YogaX at Stanford Psychiatry invites you to join us in our upco
 ming online 30-hour course\, “Therapeutic Breathwork: Pranayama for Integra
 ted Holistic Healthcare.”\n\nThe YogaX program offered through Stanford Psy
 chiatry represents an innovative fusion of yoga's ancient wisdom and the la
 test insights from modern psychological research. This in-depth therapeutic
  breathwork training delivered by lead teacher Christiane Brems investigate
 s breath and breathing as a lifestyle practice that enhances physical\, men
 tal\, and emotional health and wellbeing.\n\nThis is an advanced-level pran
 ayama course geared to the following audiences:\n\nHealthcare\, mental heal
 thcare\, and allied healthcare providers interested in bringing principles 
 and strategies of pranayama and polyvagal theory into their clinical practi
 ce.Healthcare\, mental healthcare\, and allied healthcare students in gradu
 ate or medical programs interested in bringing principles and strategies pr
 anayama into their supervised clinical practice.Yoga teachers interested in
  offering integrated holistic pranayama practices in the context of polyvag
 al theory\, especially to students and clients in healthcare and mental hea
 lthcare settings.Yoga therapists providing integrated holistic pranayama pr
 actices\, especially in healthcare and mental healthcare settings.This 30-h
 our course includes 15 hours of synchronous weekend didactic content and 15
  hours of asynchronous weekday practices. Weekend classes are scheduled for
  the following dates: \n\nMarch 29\, 8:00 am - 1:00 pm PTApril 5\, 8:00 am 
 - 1:00 pm PTApril 19\, 8:00 am - 1:00 pm PTThe full syllabus and schedule a
 re available here. Continuing Education or Advanced Professional Developmen
 t credits (30 hours) are included in the tuition cost\; STAP funds can be a
 pplied. \n\nThis 30-hour course can be taken on its own or as part of the f
 ollowing YogaX offerings: \n\n75-Hour Mental Health Certificate 300-Hour Th
 erapeutic Yoga Teacher Training300-Hour Yoga Therapeutics in Healthcare800-
 Hour Yoga Therapy TrainingIf you have any questions\, please reach out to y
 ogaxteam@stanford.edu.
