DESCRIPTION:Discover how Gallup’s U.S. Daily Tracking Poll and World Poll c
 an deepen your research.\n\nThis hybrid talk will be held on March 31st at 
 11am-12pm in the Tierney Room (121A) of Green Library. \nExplore time-serie
 s visualizations and cross-tabs available through Stanford’s Gallup Analyti
 cs subscription. The U.S. Daily Tracking Poll (2008–2016) surveyed about 7\
 ,000 adults weekly\, offering nearly 1\,900 variables and large cumulative 
 sample sizes for detailed demographic and geographic analysis. The World Po
 ll provides global insights on key issues such as safety\, food access\, go
 vernance\, employment\, and well-being.
