BEGIN:VEVENT
CATEGORIES:Class/Seminar
DESCRIPTION:Join us for a free webinar to learn how to integrate the scienc
 e of giving into your life\, ensuring that generosity remains a source of j
 oy rather than depletion. Using evidence-based strategies\, we’ll discuss h
 ow to cultivate generosity in a way that is both fulfilling and sustainable
 \, even during challenging times.\n\nMany of us devote our time\, energy\, 
 and resources to supporting others—whether family\, friends\, colleagues\, 
 patients\, or our communities. With a sustainable approach\, we can learn t
 o give with intention and lower the risk of burning out.\n\nThis engaging w
 ebinar explores the many dimensions of giving\, from financial contribution
 s to offering time\, care\, expertise\, and advocacy. We’ll examine how gen
 erosity plays a role in our daily lives\, workplaces\, and nonprofit effort
 s\, and how giving is positively associated with well-being and social conn
 ections.\n\nWhether you give professionally or personally\, this session wi
 ll provide practical insights to help you give in a sustainable way to supp
 ort both yourself and others.\n\nThis class will be recorded and a one-week
  link to the recording will be shared with all registered participants. To 
 receive incentive points\, attend at least 80% of the live session or liste
 n to the entire recording within one week.  Request disability accommodatio
 ns and access info.\n\nClass details are subject to change.
DTEND:20260410T200000Z
DTSTAMP:20260308T083912Z
DTSTART:20260410T190000Z
