DESCRIPTION:Join us for the 13th annual Stanford Center on Longevity Design
  Challenge Finals! \n\nPrevention by Design- Creating Healthy Lifestyles fo
 r Long Lives: University students globally designed solutions to empower in
 dividuals to lead healthier\, longer lives through preventive health strate
 gies.\n\nThis free event will be held in-person in Li Ka Shing Center at St
 anford University. Everyone is welcome and encouraged to attend! It will fe
 ature:\n\nPitches by the finalists showcasing their innovative designsA key
 note by Jamie Zeitzer\, Professor (Research) of Psychiatry and Behavioral S
 ciences (Sleep Medicine)\, Stanford UniversityLunch and networking opportun
 itiesAwards ceremony (1st place: $10\,000\, 2nd place: $5\,000\, 3rd place:
  $2\,000)Register here: Stanford Center on Longevity Design Challenge 2026 
 Finals April 14\, 2026\n\nCome all day or to individual events. Agenda fort
 hcoming.\n\nParking: The closest visitor and commuter parking is located in
  the Stock Farm Garage: 360 Oak Rd\, Stanford\, CA 94305. \n\nThe Stanford 
 Center on Longevity Design Challenge is a global competition aimed at encou
 raging students to design products and services to improve the lives of peo
 ple across all ages. Established in 2013\, the Challenge is focused on ways
  to motivate and empower people in their daily lives both inside their home
 s and in their community.
