BEGIN:VEVENT
CATEGORIES:Lecture/Presentation/Talk
DESCRIPTION:Join us for this Global Health Conversation with Dr. Mamphela R
 amphele\, a medical doctor\, social anthropologist\, and global public serv
 ant. She was co-founder of The Black Consciousness Movement with Steve Biko
  that reignited the struggle for freedom in South Africa.\n\nIn conversatio
 n with Global Health Faculty Fellow and veteran interviewer Paul Costello\,
  Dr. Ramphele will discuss her life\, career\, and insights on activism and
  leadership in global health worldwide.\n\nAbout Dr. Ramphele:\n\nMamphela 
 Ramphele is a world-renowned figure with an outstanding career as an activi
 st\, medical doctor\, academic\, businesswoman\, and thought leader. She wa
 s Co-President of the Club of Rome from October 2018 until end of term in N
 ovember 2023. She is the Co-Founder & Global Brand Ambassador of ReimagineS
 A since 2016. Previously\, she served as a Managing Director at the World B
 ank from 2000 to 2004 and as Vice-Chancellor of the University of Cape Town
 \, South Africa\, from 1996 to 2000.\n\nShe is a medical doctor\, a social 
 anthropologist\, and global public servant. She was Vice Chancellor of the 
 University of Cape Town\, a Managing Director at the World Bank\, and non-E
 xecutive Director of many large companies and Civil Society Organisations. 
 She is an author and recipients of many awards including 24 honorary degree
 s.\n\nDate: Tuesday April 14th\, 5-6pm\n\nLocation: Li Ka Shing Center\, LK
 SC 320\n\nIn-person only.\n\nIf you have questions\, please email globalhea
 lth@stanford.edu.
DTEND:20260415T010000Z
DTSTAMP:20260308T083912Z
