BEGIN:VEVENT
CATEGORIES:Lecture/Presentation/Talk,Other
DESCRIPTION:In this in-person session\, an admission officer provides an ov
 erview of Knight-Hennessy Scholars\, the admission process\, and the applic
 ation. The session includes a presentation\, and Knight-Hennessy scholar(s)
  may join to share their experience. \n\nAbout Knight-Hennessy Scholars\n\n
 Knight-Hennessy Scholars is a multidisciplinary\, multicultural graduate sc
 holarship program. Each Knight-Hennessy scholar receives up to three years 
 of financial support to pursue graduate studies at Stanford while participa
 ting in engaging experiences that prepare scholars to be visionary\, courag
 eous\, and collaborative leaders who address complex challenges facing the 
 world.\n\nEligibility\n\nYou are eligible to apply to the 2027 cohort of Kn
 ight-Hennessy Scholars if you earned (or will earn) your bachelor's degree 
 in 2020 or later. For military (active or veteran) applicants\, you are eli
 gible if you earned your bachelor's degree in 2018 or later. Additionally\,
  current Stanford PhD students in the first year of enrollment may apply if
  starting at KHS in the second year of PhD enrollment.\n\nDeadline\n\nThe K
 HS application to join the 2026 cohort is now closed. The KHS application t
 o join the 2027 cohort will open in summer 2026. \n\nParking\n\nParking at 
 Stanford University is free after 4:00 pm Monday-Friday. We recommend you u
 se the Tressider Lot or street parking. Please visit Stanford Transportatio
 n for more information.\n\nYou will receive details on how to join the even
 t by email following registration.
DTEND:20260425T000000Z
DTSTAMP:20260308T083913Z
DTSTART:20260424T230000Z
GEO:37.423558;-122.173774
LOCATION:Denning House
SEQUENCE:0
