BEGIN:VEVENT
CATEGORIES:Conference/Symposium
DESCRIPTION:We are excited to host Stanford’s 2nd Education Data Science Co
 nference May 27-28\, bringing together educators\, researchers\, and policy
 makers to explore what education data science research can—and should—be in
  an era of rapidly advancing technology. As generative AI makes rich educat
 ional data feel immediately actionable\, it also raises pressing questions 
 around validity\, bias\, privacy\, and pedagogical judgment. This conferenc
 e provides a forum to engage these opportunities and challenges through dia
 logue\, collaboration\, and cutting-edge research.\n\nThe program will feat
 ure a wide array of presentations on:\n\nBridging research and practice: Re
 search–practice partnerships with educators\, leaders\, and policymakers\n\
 nLLMs + multimodal/linked data: Integrating text\, audio\, video\, logs\, s
 ensors\, and administrative data\n\nScaling\, transferability\, and reprodu
 cibility: Transparent pipelines\, documentation\, and code (where feasible)
 \n\nEquity\, ethics\, privacy\, and global perspectives: Fairness\, governa
 nce\, and innovations in data-sparse contexts\n\nMore details on attending 
 the event can be found on the conference website: edsconference.stanford.ed
 u. If you are interested in presenting\, please go to the conference websit
 e for details about how to submit an abstract for consideration by January 
 5.
DTSTAMP:20260308T083914Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260527
LOCATION:
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:The Education Data Science Conference 
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_51454105357994
URL:https://events.stanford.edu/event/the-education-data-science-conference
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
CATEGORIES:Social Event/Reception,Other
DESCRIPTION:Volunteers help keep the farm running. Volunteer tasks vary fro
 m week to week. Farm tasks may include keeping our fields free of weeds and
  rocks\, planting new crop rotations\, deadheading flowers\, teaming up on 
 irrigation\, composting\, mulching\, and having a great time getting dirty.
  We ask that volunteers come prepared with close-toed shoes and clothes you
  don't mind getting dirty! We have gloves and tools for all.\n\nWe welcome 
 volunteers 10 years old and older. Those between 10 and 14 years old are re
 quired to have a guardian actively volunteering alongside them for the dura
 tion of the volunteer session.\n\nWe reserve the right to cancel volunteer 
 sessions up to two hours in advance. Possible reasons for cancelation are a
  change in COVID-19 guidelines as outlined by the University or County Offi
 cials\, excessive heat (90 degree and above)\, poor air quality\, rain or o
 ther inclement weather.\n\nWe encourage all volunteers to carpool\, bike\, 
 ride public transportation\; there is a charge for parking on all Stanford 
 property. The farm is not responsible for any tickets incurred while volunt
 eering.\n\nUPON ARRIVAL: ALL VOLUNTEERS MUST COMPLETE A SAFETY WAIVER \n\nW
 HEN YOU ARRIVE AT THE FARM: Complete Waiver Form
DTEND:20260527T190000Z
DTSTAMP:20260308T083914Z
