BEGIN:VEVENT
CATEGORIES:Class/Seminar
DESCRIPTION:Breathing is a constant in our lives from the moment we are bor
 n. It is also a subtle mirror reflecting various physical and mental imbala
 nces.\n\nBreathing properly can allow us to live longer and healthier lives
 . Breathing poorly\, by contrast\, can exacerbate and even cause a laundry 
 list of chronic diseases. By correcting and consciously working with our br
 eath\, we can calm our minds at will and improve our overall wellness.\n\nI
 n this online class\, we will focus on gaining a deeper understanding of ou
 r breath and its physiology\, drawing both from modern science and the anci
 ent system of yoga. We will discuss the mechanics of proper breathing throu
 gh the conscious relaxation of the diaphragm. We will also explore some of 
 the common unhealthy breathing habits that many tend to develop and practic
 e some effective breathing techniques and exercises to restore a state of b
 alance.\n\nThis class will not be recorded. Attendance requirement for ince
 ntive points - at least 80% of the live session.  Request disability accomm
 odations and access info.\n\nClass details are subject to change.
DTEND:20260529T223000Z
DTSTAMP:20260308T083914Z
DTSTART:20260529T210000Z
LOCATION:
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:The Healing Power of Proper Breathing
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_52220232900575
URL:https://events.stanford.edu/event/the-healing-power-of-proper-breathing
