DESCRIPTION:Welcome to Sankofa Sunday: University Praise & Worship at Stanf
 ord! The history of Black Church at Stanford dates back to 1989 when severa
 l students and the then Associate Dean Rev. Floyd Thompkins formed a worshi
 pping community to meet the spiritual and cultural yearnings of the Black C
 ommunity at Stanford. After a robust History the service was discontinued u
 ntil 2022 when the need once again led by students and staff began to reviv
 e Black Church as an occasional service once a month.
