DESCRIPTION:Created on-site at Stanford by artists from Papua New Guinea\, 
 the garden contains wood and stone carvings of people\, animals\, and magic
 al beings that illustrate clan stories and creation myths. Meet on the corn
 er of Santa Teresa and Lomita Drive.\n\nPublic Tours: Fourth Sunday of each
  month at 11:30am\, rain or shine. \n\nAdmission Info\n\nTours do not requi
 re a reservation and are free of charge.
